              <tr><td colspan="3"><hr width="100%" size="1"></td></tr>
              <tr><td colspan="3"><b>Description</b><br>
Halas is the city of snow and Halas Heaters!  Rogues, Warriors, Shamans are abound here.  This is a rather small city compared to Qeynos.  Tradeskills available are baking, pottery, alchemy, and blacksmithing.  Enjoy my land and my people.<br><br>
<b>Player Comments</b> (total:6, showing:1-5) <a href="JavaScript:popComment('comment.php3?type=zone&tid=10')">add</a><br>
<a href="mailto:ShamanBaila@yahoo.com">Baila</a> of the Quellious server on Oct. 05, 2000 at 12:55pm said...<br>
The North Tower also called Megan's Tower is a good place for one from level 10-14 to hunt.  Orc Troopers shall cross yer path and if you take two of their arm bands to Cindl, she'll give you armor and coin.  Beware their Shaman, for they can root ye and strike ye down quicker than Iceberg can gobble down some Lion Delight.  If ye be brave, or have friends, head to the South Tower at level 13 and above to take down Orc Mountaineers and ice boned skeletons.  Lastly, as any good Barbarian knows, Lixt wing stalks dropped by the orc are needed by Shamans 'o Justice.  Sell them at the Shaman guild to the lovely lasses outside and you should get a higher price than you will elsewhere in Halas or Everfrost.  The price won't be better by much, but every last gold and silver piece counts.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:manderson@nxs.net">Ahnvil Frostforge</a> of the Bristlebane server on Oct. 04, 2000 at 04:18pm said...<br>
If indeed killing Snowflake raises Banker faction, you can ask Snowflake the phrase "Where is Meagan?" and the wolf will walk out into the Tundra to the Tundra Jack and Iceberg's tower<br><br>
<a href="mailto:charixz@mailcity.com">Vurkanan Tyes</a> of the POVAR server on Dec. 21, 1999 at 02:18pm said...<br>
As mentioned already, the polar bear skin quest to tailor & Karg Icebear is a great money/xp getter.  Also collect all the wolly fungus you can as every 8 gets a level 1-5 shaman spell from the shaman trainer to the extreme left of the door to the guild.  Also take note when you begin killing gnolls at the entrance to the foul lair of the Blackburrow Gnolls to take & hold the teeth as every 3 given to the female guild master in warriors arena in Halas willget you some common items and xp and the all important factions for our fair town.  This will help when around level 20 you venture out in West Kanara to kil the murder Basil or Paglan on the quest to obtain the Langseaux or Langseaux of the Wolves swords (highly sought by other races, warrior only).  The banker does indeed have sympathies with the evils of the land and doing quests repeatedly will get you levels faster but you will soon find yourself like me unable to enter that building anymore as he will Kill you On Sight (KOS).<br><br>
<a href="mailto:UOAvatar@msn.com">Heimdall</a> of the Rodcet Nife server on Dec. 10, 1999 at 05:17pm said...<br>
Be extremely careful turning in the pelt for armor directly.  It's better to just sell it. and then buy armor.  The Banker seems to have a problem with anything improving the security and prowess of Halas warriors.  Any completeled quest tends to make him like you less, however if you find snowflake and can figure out how to take him out to the Tundra killing him is something that pleases the Banker.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:shaka@harrowing.com">Boomshaka Laka</a> of the Xegony server on Dec. 08, 1999 at 07:34pm said...<br>
Halas be the home o' the hearty folk o' the Norrath, the mighty Wolves o' the North.  There are many a' quests to be done, and many a' critter to be kilt in our frozen land.  Likely the reason why our Barbarians are so feared and respected the world over, is our young'uns area be one o' the most fertile, profitable, and exciting there be.  Our pups can hunt the Everfrost peaks well into 7th level, and then the tundra can take them through 15th with nary a wit o' trouble or boredom.  And as to the tailor mentioned above who collects the white bear pelts, Cindl be her name.  She's a bonny lass, my third cousin on me father's side she is...<br><br>
<center>0 - <a href="zone.php3?tag=halas&pg=1">1</a></center></td></tr>
